Bug: Polysorbate 80 CoA extraction returns contradictory JSON:
- eg_present=Yes but eg_specification_limit=null and eg_source=not_mentioned
- raw_text says "No DEG or EG testing mentioned" which is factually wrong
- 620 ppm value on page 2 of CoA never extracted

Root cause: converter reads page 1 only; LLM allowed to output Yes+null+
not_mentioned contradiction; multi-page merge missing.

Fix 1 — Complete multi-page merge in convert_deg_eg_pdf_to_json:
After extracting page 1 metadata via deg_eg_meta_prompt, iterate pages 2..N
calling deg_eg_page_prompt. When a later page returns a real limit OR a real
source (vendor_coa/vendor_spec/usp_469), OVERRIDE page-1 defaults for that
glycol. Merge declaration_scopes across pages. Concatenate raw_text.

Fix 2 — Add strict consistency rules to deg_eg_meta_prompt and
deg_eg_page_prompt:
- present=Yes REQUIRES source in (vendor_coa, vendor_spec, usp_469)
- present=Yes REQUIRES non-null numeric limit string
- Never emit Yes with limit=null or source=not_mentioned
- If numeric limit cannot be extracted after scanning ALL pages, output Unknown
- Scan for patterns: "Not more than X ppm", "NMT X ppm", "X PPM MAX", "≤ X ppm",
  "0.X%" (convert 0.5%=5000 ppm)
- Scan sections titled "Residual solvents", "12. Residual solvents", numbered
  subsections, "Impurities", "Specifications", "Tests"

Fix 3 — Post-processing consistency guard in process_deg_eg_annexure:
For each glycol (deg/eg):
- If present=Yes but source in ("not_mentioned", "") → downgrade to Unknown
- If present=Yes but limit is null/empty → downgrade to Unknown
- Log warning when downgrading

