FIX 4 — Material code (DRL SAP code) extraction and validation:

Bug: Table 2 material code column shows wrong values or blanks:
- Vendor internal codes (e.g. Ashland "431216") used instead of DRL SAP code
- Batch numbers (e.g. Roquette "722961") used instead of SAP code
- Vendor Material Numbers (e.g. CP Kelco "20055915") used instead of SAP code
- Six materials show blank codes even though SAP codes are visible on CoAs

Root cause: converter has no explicit rule to prefer "SAP CODE:" label over
other numeric labels; multi-page CoAs may have SAP code on a different page
than the label the LLM latched onto.

Fix 4a — Add strict SAP code rules to deg_eg_meta_prompt:
Look for the DRL SAP material code with strict priority:
1. Label "SAP CODE:" or "SAP Code:" followed by 6-9 digit number
2. Label "Material Code:" followed by a number starting with 10000/20000/
   30000/35000 (DRL SAP pattern)
3. Label "Product Code:" followed by a 6-9 digit DRL-style number

Never use as material_code:
- Vendor internal codes (Ashland Material Number, CP Kelco Material Number,
  Roquette Material Code, etc.)
- Batch/Lot numbers, Order numbers, Delivery numbers
- Customer material numbers, GRN numbers, A.R. numbers, ATR numbers
- Specification numbers (SP-CFTO-XXXXXX — these go to drl_specification_no
  field, not material_code)
- CAS numbers (these go to cas_number field, not material_code)

If no SAP CODE label found, leave material_code EMPTY. Never substitute.

Scan ALL pages of the CoA. SAP codes often appear in a footer block or on
page 2+, not necessarily near the material name.

Fix 4b — Add new fields to converter output schema:
{
  "material_code": "",              // DRL SAP code only
  "material_code_source": "sap_code|not_found",
  "cas_number": "",                 // separate field
  "drl_specification_no": "",       // SP-CFTO-XXXXXX-N pattern if not available leave empty
  ...
}

Fix 4c — Post-processing validation in process_deg_eg_annexure:
- Validate material_code matches DRL SAP pattern: ^(1000|2000|3000|3500)\d{4,5}$
- If it doesn't match, discard (set empty)
- Validate drl_specification_no matches ^SP-[A-Z]{2,4}-?\d{6,10}(-\d+)?$
- If it doesn't match, discard
- Validate cas_number matches ^\d{1,7}-\d{2}-\d$
- If it doesn't match, discard

Fix 4d — Wire material_code into assessment table:
When building Table 2 rows, use ann.get("material_code") from the matched
annexure. If empty, leave the cell blank. Never auto-generate M001-M999
sequential codes.

Fix 4e — Wire drl_specification_no into detail tables:
When building Table 3+ detail tables for positive materials, populate the
"DRL Specification No." column with ann.get("drl_specification_no") + "*"
suffix. If empty, leave blank.

